description: Auriol Grey, 49, swiped angrily at 77-year-old Celia Ward (pictured) and told her to 'get off the f****** pavement' moments before the crash in Huntingdon, Cambridgeshire.

title: Taha Sabbagh family flood Sefton street in Sydney after he was shot dead at Elite Fight Force gym
description: Taha Sabbagh, 40, was shot dead outside the Elite Fight Force gym on Carlingford Street, in Sefton, western Sydney, about 6.30am on Thursday and hours later dozens of angry loved ones arrived.

title: Australia's richest person denies she is behind $544m super fund
description: Gina Rinehart, 69, has said she is not the person with more than half a billion in her pension pot.

title: Husky rescued after spending 23 days trapped under Turkey earthquake rubble
description: Alex the husky was pulled from the wreckage by rescue teams in Antakya in the province of Hatay after they overheard him while carrying out searches nearby.

title: Experts call out LDV eT60 electric ute
description: Questions have been raised about Australia's first electric ute amid claims the vehicle is not suitable for farmers and agricultural work.

title: Delta agrees 34% pay rise for pilots with other major airlines set to follow suit
description: The Air Line Pilots Association said 78 percent of Delta's 15,000 pilots voted to support the contract which will lead to a cumulative $7 billion in pay raises.

title: Journalist who leaked Matt Hancock's WhatsApp messages sent 'threatening' and 'menacing' message
description: Isabel Oakeshott (right) said she was sent the 'threatening' message by Matt Hancock (left) in the early hours of Wednesday evening, after giving him no advance warning of the messages' publication.

title: Man, 50, who sold guns to gangsters across Britain using EncroChat system jailed for 19 years
description: Michael Derrane, 50, from Morpeth in Northumberland, transferred firearms and multiple kilos of class A and B drugs to crime groups for a profit, according to the NCA.

title: ABC staff demand more taxpayer money as they prepare to go on strike
description: Staff will hold a 40 minute strike next Tuesday after they rejected the taxpayer-funded national broadcaster's offer of 10.5 per cent pay rise over three years with a $1500 one-off payment.

title: 'Bomb' almost smuggled onto passenger plane was a commercial grade firework
description: Mark Muffley, 40, of Lansford, Pennsylvania, was arrested on Monday for allegedly bringing a 'bomb' onto an Allegiant flight.

title: Minot Air Force Base officials fired over 'loss of confidence' after failed security test
description: Two commanders and four subordinates in the United States Air Force were fired this week after their base failed safety and security inspections pertaining to the nuclear stockpile.

title: Paedophile, 46, is jailed after former victim 'traps' him on a child rape website
description: The woman, who had been abused by Hugo De Sousa as a child, discovered in 2021 he had been convicted of distributing and making images of child sex abuse.

title: Biden LAUGHS at MTG blaming him for overdoses of two brothers - they died under Trump
description: Biden laughed off a claim from Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene that he 'killed' a mother's two sons who died of fentanyl in 2020 even they'd died during the Trump administration.

title: Parole DENIED for Robert F. Kennedy's assassin Sirhan Sirhan, 78
description: A panel denied parole for RFK assassin Sirhan Sirhan on the grounds that the 78-year-old prisoner continues to lack insight into what caused him to shoot the senator in 1968.

title: Holiday home owners in Scotland face new SNP tax hike from First Minister frontrunner
description: First Minister frontrunner Humza Yousaf (pictured) said yesterday he would give local authorities the power to force owners of second homes to pay higher council tax bills.

title: Harry and Meghan eviction 'has sparked row between working and non-working royals'
description: It emerged on Monday that the Sussexes had been issued an eviction notice to leave the five-bedroom mansion - a stone's throw away from the principal residence of the Prince and Princess of Wales.

title: British ministers should go after Brexit opportunities more forcefully, says Ron DeSantis
description: Florida Governor Ron DeSantis revealed he is a 'big supporter' of Britain's decision to leave the EU.

title: Whoopi Goldberg says 'politics got in the way' of truth as she discusses Covid lab leak theory
description: Whoopi Goldberg has weighed into the row over whether Covid-19 originated from a lab in Wuhan, declaring 'politics got in the way' of truth.

title: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: This self-harming tax rise shames the Chancellor
description: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: During the Tory leadership race in the summer, one candidate proposed a radical plan to turbocharge the economy: Slash corporation tax to 15 per cent.

title: Angry passengers lose it at Jetstar after waiting for more than five hours for flight to Bali
description: Jetstar has come under fire once more after passengers for a flight to Bali were left waiting for more than five hours - before it was cancelled for the day.

title: EPHRAIM HARDCASTLE: Prince William's potentially awkward visit to homelessness charity
description: EPHRAIM HARDCASTLE: Prince William's visit to the homelessness charity The Passage had to be handled sensitively by aides.

title: Spy chiefs face calls to release data on Covid origins amid FBI theory virus leaked from Chinese lab
description: British spy chiefs faced calls yesterday to release intelligence on the origins of Covid-19 and end a 'conspiracy of silence' on the matter in the UK.

title: Police are accused of spending the equivalent of only ONE day a week fighting crime
description: The Crown Prosecution Service's Gregor McGill said officers typically spend just 20 per cent of their time on 'criminal justice'.

title: Lisa Wilkinson must PROVE Brittany Higgins was raped by Bruce Lehrmann to win defamation case
description: Bruce Lehrmann launched a defamation suit against Lisa Wilkinson and the network over an interview aired on The Project on February 15, 2021, where Ms Higgins first alleged she was raped.

title: Shortages of groceries on supermarket shelves have led to a rush of people wanting to grow their own
description: The RHS said searches on its website's fruit and vegetable pages are up 20% compared to this time last year as would-be growers read up on how to start vegetable patches.

title: Call for mum of baby given a vape to inhale to be jailed - as police visit Kempsey, NSW home
description: A call for the parents or carers of the 10-month-old baby fed a vape to be jailed has been made, with the act being labelled 'child abuse'. Police have visited a Kempsey home on the NSW Mid North Coast.

title: GOP resolution demands Pete Buttigieg RESIGN for response to Ohio train derailment
description: Now that Congress is back in session, lawmakers are taking into their own hands remediation efforts for East Palestine, Ohio - including a resolution demanding Transportation Secretary Pete Buttigieg resign.

title: Keir Starmer sets his gaze on Partygate investigator Sue Gray to become his new chief of staff
description: Labour leader Sir Keir Starmer is hoping to recruit Cabinet Office enforcer Sue Gray as his new chief of staff, according to Sky News.

title: Freedom of the Press will not be stifled by controversial new anti-spying law, minister insists
description: Lord Sharpe of Epsom said journalists would not be prosecuted for writing articles critical of the Government that might assist hostile states, nor for handling leaked documents.
